ISSUE 1 — ngrok ERR_NGROK_15013
---------------------------------
Error   : "Your account is requesting a dev domain that does not exist."
Cause   : The ngrok account previously had a free static domain reserved
          (e.g. something.ngrok-free.app) that was deleted or expired.
          ngrok v3 always tries to reuse that domain and fails if it no
          longer exists at the account level.
Fix     : Switched to localtunnel (via npx) as the tunnel provider.
          ngrok can be re-enabled by going to:
          https://dashboard.ngrok.com/domains → "New Domain" → claim a
          free static domain → then run:
            "D:\ngrok-v3-stable-windows-amd64\ngrok.exe" http 8001

ISSUE 2 — ngrok override config not found on first pass
---------------------------------------------------------
Error   : "open d:\Email Sender Agent\cv-agent\ngrok-override.yml:
          The system cannot find the file specified."
Cause   : The override config file was created after ngrok had already
          launched (race condition between Write and background process).
Fix     : Non-issue once we switched to localtunnel.

